reviewText: Hee Haw is back Yeah.  I grew up watching Hee Haw before I really liked country music.  I watched it for the great actors on the show and the comedy.  I really learned to love country music from watching Hee Haw.  The salute to Hee Haw is awesome.  The have some of the best moments from the early years on Hee Haw.  Hee Haw was on CBS for a few years, until CBS decided to cancel all of it's shows with "trees" in them.  They canned Petticoat Junction, Green Acres, and the Beverly Hillbillies.  Hee Haw went into syndication and thrived lasting over 20 years.  Check out the interviews on the last disc.  There are wonderful interviews with Roy Clark, Ronnie Stoneman, Lulu Roman, Hager twins, and George Lindsay.  Watching these DVD's makes m want to order more in the Hee Haw series.  I wish there was something like Hee Haw on TV today.

reviewText: If you like Country Music like me you will love The Hee Haw Collection I've got many Episodes and they are Great Fun to Watch. The Shows are Beautifully Transferred to DVD. The Colors are very Clear Bright and Colorful The Sound is very Strong and Powerful considering some of these Shows go back to 1969The Hee Haw Show were a Summer replacement Series for The Smothers Brothers Comedy Hour. Each week co-host Buck Owens and Roy Clark and the Cast of Comedians and Musicians would Welcome the Biggest Stars in Country Music to perform their Songs and help deliver the One-LinersThe Hee Haw Collection 5 Discs 8 EpisodesDISC (1)Episode: 15 - 1969 Dottie West, Hank Williams Jr.Episode: 19 - 1970 Merle Haggard Loretta LynnDISC (2)Episode: 9 -- 1969 Jerry Lee Lewis, Conway TwittyEpisode: 32 - 1970 Ray Charles, Lynn AndersonDISC (3)Episode: 42 - 1970 Waylon Jennings, Johnny DuncanEpisode: 43 - 1970 Roy Rogers and Dale EvansDISC (4)Episode: 108- 1973 Tanya Tucker, Buddy AlanEpisode: 126- 1974 Loretta Lynn, Conway TwittyDISC (5) Interview with Various Artists:Roy Clark, The Hagger Twins, George Lindsey and othersHee Haw Ranked in the Top 20 Nationwide, Every Episode is about 50 Minutes Long, I never get tired of watching Hee Haw and the Old Style of Country Music with the Original Instruments nothing like today, most Artists don't even use the Steel Guitar any more which by the way it goes back to 1922 and earlier. The Hee Haw Collection Episodes are part of American Musical History and I Love to be able to Watch them and Collect them.. Thank You D.D.
